LAGOS – The Federal government has said it will continue to sustain efforts through the National Directorate of Employment, (NDE), to create opportunities for unemployed youths to en­able them to empower them­selves and become self-suffi­cient. Mallam Abubakar Fikpo, Director General, NDE, stated this in Asaba, Delta State on the occasion of the orientation of the loan beneficiaries of the schemes under the Rural Em­ployment Promotion, (REP), and department of the NDE. He advised that unemployed youths should go into agricul­ture to produce abundant food locally for the teeming popu­lation in order to reduce food importation to Nigeria. Kogi: Angry Mob Sets Police Barrack Ablaze Over Slain Boy NAWOJ Advocates Justice For Hanifa, Others He said through agribusi­ness engagements, such as the Sustainable Agricultural De­velopment and Empowerment Scheme, (SADES), Community Based Agricultural Empow­erment Scheme, (CBADE), Agricultural Enhancement Scheme, (AES), and Graduate Agricultural Empowerment Scheme, (GAES) were created specifically to empower the trainees who have graduated under the sustainable agricul­ture and improve their living standard, especially in the ru­ral areas. Represented by Eden Duke, Deputy Director, REP department, while saying the sole purpose of the loan disbursement is to encourage the trainees to start up their entrepreneurship through planting crops, livestock and all other agric value change. He added that they could equally diversify to produc­tion, packaging, processing, and marketing and even to consumption.